item.description:
Livelihood (making a living) means the desire for sustenance and the effort to obtain it. &ldquo;Livelihood&rdquo; (ma&rsquo;ash) is a maf&rsquo;al formation from `aysh &ldquo;life.&rdquo;
The idea is that &lsquo;aysh &ldquo;life&rdquo; is obtained only through the things that go into making a living, and they are therefore considered, with some exaggeration, &ldquo;the place of life.&rdquo; 14
Sustenance and profit may be obtained - through- having the power to take them away from others and to appropriate them according to a generally recognized norm.

This is because agriculture is a natural and simple procedure. As a rule, sedentary people, or people who live in luxury, do not practice it. Those who practice it are characterized by humility.
When Muhammad saw a plowshare in one of the houses of the Ansar (in Medina). He said= &ldquo;Such a thing never entered anyone&rsquo;s house save accompanied by humbleness.&rdquo;
Al-Bukhari explained this (statement) as referring to too intense an occupation with (agriculture) and he entitled the chapter in which he dealt with the tradition in question= &ldquo;Warning against the consequences of (too intensive an) occupation with agricultural implements or transgression of the stipulated limit.
